  "1,000,000, particularly": "",
  "2,500, particularly": "",
  "50,000, particularly": "",
  "A rank-50 SVD stores U_50 (1000 x 50 = 50,000 values), 50 singular values, and V_50 (1000 x 50 = 50,000 values), totaling 100,050 values. This is about 10% of the original 1,000,000 entries, achieving significant compression.": "",
  "A social network analyst constructs a 5000x5000 adjacency matrix A where A[i][j] = 1 if users i and j are friends. She computes the eigenvalues and finds two dominant eigenvalues with a large gap to the rest. What does this suggest about the network?": "",
